<paragraph id="79085C025967581258B6C2A4FA875392" blockId="4.[166,1225,660,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">
The species is known so far from the Talysh Mountains in 
<collectingCountry id="01A01C92596758125BFAC2A4FD3253D3" box="[919,1050,660,686]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
, from where it was described by Reitter in 1884 under the name 
<taxonomicName id="BEB72781596758125A85C285FA7053B2" box="[744,856,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Cis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setifer">
<emphasis id="4BC38010596758125A85C285FA7053B2" box="[744,856,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Cis setifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The host fungus is unknown. D i s t r i b u t i o n: 
<collectingCountry id="01A01C925967581259F7C2E4FB325393" box="[410,538,724,750]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1D2621F3596758125A44C2E4FBEE5392" author="Jelinek, J." box="[553,710,724,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="321" pagination="55 - 62" refId="ref7331" refString="Jelinek, J. 2008. Family Ciidae Leach, 1819. In: Lobl, I. and Smetana, A., eds. Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Vol. 5, Tenebrionoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 55 - 62." type="book chapter" year="2008">Jelínek, 2008</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry id="01A01C92596758125AB4C2E5FA235392" box="[729,779,725,751]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Iran</collectingCountry>
(first record).
</paragraph>
